                            <comment id="19249" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2006 04:10:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed... this invocation happened outside of a try-catch block. I&apos;ve added it to the general try-catch block that we use for the bean instantiation process, so any such exception should get wrapped in a BeanCreationException (the expected type) now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
